<promed@promedmail.org>

[Epizootic hemorrhagic disease (EHD) is closely related to bluetongue virus
infection (BTV). Both diseases are carried by biting midges. Recently
Europe has experienced a significant upswing in BTV. It also moved further
north than had previously been thought possible. EHD may be following a
similar pattern. This could indicate the virus is changing its virulence or
has become more resistant to cold weather [climate change? - Mod.SH]. The
virus has, in some way, changed its character. As such it means
veterinarians and producers in more regions not previously seeing EHD will
now need to add this disease to their differential list. - Mod.TG]
